[I] Daemon that finds starving tasks and gives them a temporary boost

[T] The stalld program (which stands for 'stall daemon') is a mechanism to
[T] prevent the starvation of operating system threads in a Linux system.

[U] https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/utils/stalld/stalld.git/

